<h1>Introduction</h1>
<p>Napoleon was one of the finest generals ever to walk the Earth. His military career coincided with the aftermath of the French Revolution, and indeed one of his first ever military actions was to deploy cannon to disperse protestors on the streets of Paris. He led armies across Europe, from the frozen wastes of Russia to the scorching deserts of Egypt, leaving a trail of destruction and blood as he went. Under his leadership, Revolutionary France fought against almost the entirety of Europe, and, on numerous occasions, was victorious. </p>
